public class LayoutEvent
extends com.google.gwt.event.shared.GwtEvent<LayoutEvent.Handler>

Event to notify that a layout operation occurred on a Rhizosphere visualization. This includes both changes to the layout algorithm and manual model repositionings by the user.

Author:
battlehorse@google.com (Riccardo Govoni)

Method Detail

getEngine

public java.lang.String getEngine()
Returns:
The layout engine currently in use by the visualization. The returned string is one the valid engine names as defined in rhizo.layout.js in the rhizo.layout.layouts structure.

getState

public com.google.gwt.json.client.JSONObject getState()
Returns:
The current layout engine state. The state is the set of configuration options that each layout engine accepts to customize its behavior. The state definition is layout-specific.

getPositions

public java.util.Collection<RhizosphereModelPosition> getPositions()
Returns:
An collection of explicit positioning of visualization models, that overrides the default position otherwise computed by the layout engine.

fire

public static void fire(HasLayoutHandlers source,
                        java.lang.String engine,
                        com.google.gwt.json.client.JSONObject state,
                        java.util.Collection<RhizosphereModelPosition> positions)
Fires a LayoutEvent on all registered handlers in the handler source.

Parameters:
source - the source of the handlers
engine - The layout engine to use, or null to reuse the current one.
state - The layout state to use, or null to reuse the current one.
positions - An optional collection of explicit positioning information for visualization models, that will override any position the layout engine would otherwise define. Leave null if unneeded.
